        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17023",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shreef",
                        "name": "shreef",
                        "displayName": "Ahmed Shreef",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "We weren't planing to add functunality like that when we were designing the API, but it appears to be important now.\ninstead of creating new instance methods with weird names to get over this, we will use the old static methods by passing it an instance of your Zend_Currency object as a 1st param.\n\nlike this\n{code}\n\n$Dollar = new Zend_Currency('en_US');\n\n\/\/ the old way, it still works . will print \u062c.\u0645.\necho Zend_Currency::getSymbol('ar_EG');\n\n\/\/ the new way, you pass it a Zend_Currency instance\necho Zend_Currency::getSymbol($Dollar); \/\/prints $\n{code}\n\nthe new way saves you from calling Zend_Locale_Data::getContent() again and again..\n\nthe new feature added in svn-6553\n\nthanx =)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shreef",
                        "name": "shreef",
                        "displayName": "Ahmed Shreef",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-30T05:02:02.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-30T05:02:02.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17026",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nataniel",
                        "name": "nataniel",
                        "displayName": "Artur Jedlinski",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "That's probably the best way without breaking the backward compatibility and it's the step in right direction, but I'm not huge fan of it. In real-life project you have a currency and you want to display all values in it (for example in online store)... Now if you want to display it like 200.00 USD (using the shortName instead of symbol), you have to:\n{code}echo $myCurrency->toCurrency(200).' '.Zend_Currency::getShortName($myCurrency);{code}\nwhen preferred way would be:\n{code}echo $myCurrency->toCurrency(200).' '.$myCurrency->getShortName(){code}\nor even better\n{code}echo $myCurrency->toCurrency(200, null, null, Zend_Currency::USE_SHORTNAME){code}\n\nThe other problem is that currently you cannot really display 200.00 USD, just 200 USD, because you don't have a way to set precision. Currency is most often displayed with 2-digits precision (like prices), so it's very common use - very hard to do with current version :) I've added setPrecision() and ::setDefaultPrecision() to my extension of the class, maybe that's some kind of solution.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nataniel",
                        "name": "nataniel",
                        "displayName": "Artur Jedlinski",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-30T06:08:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-30T06:08:38.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17028",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I was already reworking the whole class.\nNow I have to rework my already made changes which have taken two days.\n\nPlease ask always before reassigning any issue already assigned to another person.\n\nYou should never close a issue where no unit tests and no documentation has been added.\nChanges to the API as made here have to be thought of precise !\n\nThank you.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-30T06:42:33.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-30T06:42:33.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17029",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shreef",
                        "name": "shreef",
                        "displayName": "Ahmed Shreef",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "hay Thomas,\n\nsorry, you didn't inform me about the rework of the class so I started fixing the bugs that you didn't mark as 'in progress'. sorry again.\n\n{quote}\nYou should never close a issue where no unit tests and no documentation has been added.\n{quote}\n\nI commited the unit tests with my fix. the code were tested and didn't break the API and I was working on the docs.\n\nThanks",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shreef",
                        "name": "shreef",
                        "displayName": "Ahmed Shreef",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-30T08:27:22.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-30T08:27:22.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17032",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "No problem ahmed...\n\nSorry for being angry. I've worked the whole night until 3am for the new class and saw your comment after a short night. SVN did not send me the changes so there's also a problem with the server.\n\nAs solution we came to the following solution:\n\n * All internal variables have been changed to be within an array (_options) which is protected.\n * But without the locale... we have a defined get and set for this one as for all other I18N classes.\n * Code was internally complete reworked.\n * The constructor does no longer support script.\n * The setFormat method has been reworked to accept an options array\n * Script can be set through the options\n * A new option 'precision' has been added, standardvalue 2\n * Completly reworked the testbed\n\nI will commit everything when the code is ready.\n\nStill thinking about the static issue... I want to solve all 3 issues at once.\nWhen you have a idea just come out with it.\n\nPHP should be able to have a static and an instance method of the same name... then we would not have the problem ;-)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-30T15:21:48.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-30T15:21:48.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17033",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nataniel",
                        "name": "nataniel",
                        "displayName": "Artur Jedlinski",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm not sure the static methods are needed at all. It's very simple to create an instance and run methods from it. I see no need for the statics, they are pretty confusing (you would really expect them to be not static at all).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nataniel",
                        "name": "nataniel",
                        "displayName": "Artur Jedlinski",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-10-01T03:02:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-10-01T03:02:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17059",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shreef",
                        "name": "shreef",
                        "displayName": "Ahmed Shreef",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thomas, good work :) . I'm waiting your commit. and like what Artur said, we can turn (getSymbol, getName and getShortName) into instance methods if it's possible now.\n\n{quote}\nPHP should be able to have a static and an instance method of the same name... then we would not have the problem ;)\n{quote}\n\nwe can call instance methods as static methods, but it raises error only when error_reporting set to E_STRICT.\n\n{code}\n\nclass me {\n\n    public function go() {\n\n        if( isset($this) ) {\n            print '- instance';\n        } else {\n            print '- static';\n        }\n\n    }\n\n}\n\nme::go();\n\n$me = new me() ;\n\n$me->go();\n\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shreef",
                        "name": "shreef",
                        "displayName": "Ahmed Shreef",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-10-04T07:38:01.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-10-04T07:38:01.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17076",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I am finished with code and unittests.\nExcept for the static\/instance issue.\n\nI have to write additional documentation (for 1.0.2 -> 1.0.3 changes) before I can commit it to trunk.\nI think you can test it in about 2 days.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-10-04T16:56:59.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-10-04T16:56:59.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17084",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The API has been completly reworked which includes this issue.\n\nPlease review and test SVN 6597 or later and give us response.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
